      "repair_reason": "- [P1] No automated repair is appropriate because the remaining blocker is contributor-supplied real behavior proof, not a code change.; Cleared: The diff only changes cleanup in an existing Ollama stream path and adds a local proof script; it does not add dependencies, workflows, secrets handling, package metadata, or broader code-execution surface. (sha=92fd232c9397893d9755557e0afcd04eedf8bea4)",
      "review_summary": "This PR hoists the Ollama response-body reader into outer scope, releases its lock during cleanup, and adds a standalone Web Streams lock proof script.\n\nPR surface: Source +4, Tests +63. Total +67 across 2 files.\n\nReproducibility: yes. at source level: current main acquires a ReadableStream reader in the Ollama chat stream path and does not release the reader lock, and a Node Web Streams probe confirms cancel does not unlock. A real failing Ollama run has not been established.",
